    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Tile game of Chinese origin usually played by four players with 144 dominolike pieces or tiles marked in suites,  counters, and dice, the object being to collect winning combinations of tiles.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000000/VP</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000046684/Random House Unabridged Dictionary (1993)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>源自中國，通常由四位玩家運用144顆形似骨牌外觀的麻將牌進行。藉由麻將牌置換、取捨拼出成對、順號等方式取得獲勝的組合牌型。
</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>Chinese (traditional)</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000250/AS-Academia Sinica</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
        <Note_Sources>
          <Note_Source>
            <Source>
              <Source_ID>2000079740/AS-Academia Sinica data (2014-)</Source_ID>
            </Source>
          </Note_Source>
        </Note_Sources>
      </Descriptive_Note>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Ein Legespiel chinesischen Ursprungs, das normalerweise von vier Spielern mit 144 dominoartigen Legesteinen gespielt wird. Diese sind mit Farben, Zählern und Würfeln gekennzeichnet. Das Ziel besteht darin, Gewinnkombinationen aus Legesteinen zu sammeln.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>German</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
          <Note_Contributor>
            <Contributor_id>10000232/IfM-SMB-PK</Contributor_id>
          </Note_Contributor>
        </Note_Contributors>
